      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Organized in November 1825 as the Baptist Church of Christ
         at Chaney's Chapel. Sometime prior to July 1833, the name was
         changed to Shiloh.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>These minutes cover the period from November 1825 to 15
         March 1873. They record in detail the church's concern with
         the problems of the times, such as the question of foreign
         missions, the tragedy of the Civil War, and matters related to
         black members after the war. Membership lists appear on page 7
         (members who organized the church at Chaney's Chapel), and
         240-351 (1825-1873).</p>
      </scopecontent>
